  "texts": [
    "To approach this task, we propose a novel inverse reinforcement learning framework that sets up an adversarial interaction between a policy and a relativistic critic: the policy learns to mimic expert answers, while the critic learns to discriminate between policy and expert answers via pairwise comparison.",
    "By jointly training both the policy and the critic to reason via RL, we enable the emergence of strong reasoning capabilities from demonstrations alone, without requiring task-specific verifiers.",
    "Let D = {(q i, a i)} n i=1 denote the expert QA dataset.",
    "We parameterize our LLM policy as π θ (a, z | q), a distribution over answers a and Chain-of-Thought (CoT) reasonings z conditioned on a question q.",
    "We let pq (•) denote the empirical distribution of questions in D, pa|q (• | •) denote the empirical distribution of expert answers conditioned on a question, and the joint pD = pa|q pq denote the empirical distribution of dataset pairs (q, a)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}